	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=6447&mid=107890162659214>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6447&mid=107890162659214>Anger aug's and aggro weapons</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6447&mid=107890162659214#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Mar 10th 1:54 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=228459><span id= >Walgurorf</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>OK this is the deal with the EB proc on the BoC and the Anger range of aggro aug's from LDoN.<br><br>1/ No it is not a waste putting anger aug on a BoC<br>2/ No they don't stack<br><br>What I mean by that is on each attack round the system will check if the 1st proc takes effect, now if it does thats it, nothing more will happen untill the next attack round. If however it doesn't proc, it will then check if the 2nd effect takes place (in this case the Anger aug). Therefore the Anger aug will only proc if the Enraging Blow effect doesn't (this is true for all weapons with 2 (Combat) effects, whether it's aggro, DD, slow or whatever).<br><br>Effectively adding an Anger aug will at least double the chance of an aggro effect taking place, I say at least double because in my own experience the Anger 3 aug procs more often then the original BoC proc.</p>&nbsp;<br>Walgurorf Beawulfe<br>65 Overlord Karana<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=651187 target=akztarg>My Magelo</a></td></td></tr>
